Mo’believe, one of the beneficiaries of Mr Eazi‘s emPawa100 program which assists 100 budding talents from across Africa realize their dream by shooting and marketing videos, has released the video for the remix of his track Bí Oba off his debut Project “Ariwo eko” (Noise of Lagos). On this project, Mo’believe tries to document the sounds that we always forget to remember in the city. The video was shot by Adasa Cookey for Squareball Media. Watch: The post New Video: Mo’believe – Bí Oba (Remix) appeared first on BellaNaija – Showcasing Africa to the world. Read today!. Source: Bella Naija